Title: Hide classes
Describe: None
------------------------------------------------------------
[Example]
None

[Description]
You can also use the `show/hide` commands to hide classes.
This may be useful if you define a large ,
and if you want to hide some classes after .

[UML]
@startuml

class Foo1
class Foo2

Foo2 *-- Foo1

hide Foo2

@enduml
